original_title: Bronx: White Plains Road - Westchester Avenue
text:
White Plains Road, north from Westchester Ave. In the background is visible the Unionport Road bridge over the tracks of the New York, New Haven and Hartford Railroad.

James Suydam.

About 1915.

E. 177th Street, north side, east from White Plains Road to Westchester Avenue, showing, on the latter, the elevated station of the I.R.T. subway.

View 1: April 10, 1938.
View v: September 4, 1939

P.L. Sperr

View v shows the same area, looking west from near Westchester Avenue toward White Plains Road. Under construction are units of "Parkchester," the new development by the Metropolitan Life Insurance Company.
